text: Haifa Wehbe (, born 10 March 1972) is a female Lebanese-Egyptian singer, actress, model, and jewelry designer who is known in the Arab world. Wehbe was born in a rural town in South Lebanon and currently lives in Beirut. She started her music career with her debut album Huwa az-Zaman (, It is Time). == Early life and career == Before she became a singer, she was a model. She won title "Miss South Lebanon" when she was sixteen. In 1995, she was the runner- up for Miss Lebanon before the public found out she had a daughter named Zeinab. Her second 2005 album was Baddi 'Ay≈° (, I Want to Live). Her second songs was "Ana Haifa" (I am Haifa).
